  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is useState?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "useState is a React Hook that allows you to add state to functional components."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const [state, setState] = useState(initialValue);"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import { useState } from 'react';\n\nfunction Counter() {\n  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);\n\n  return (\n    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>\n      {count}\n    </button>\n  );\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Updating State"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "setCount(prev => prev + 1);"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Multiple States"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const [name, setName] = useState('');\nconst [age, setAge] = useState(0);"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "State with Objects"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const [user, setUser] = useState({ name: '', age: 0 });\n\nsetUser({ ...user, name: 'John' });"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use functional updates when needed**",
        "**Keep state minimal**",
        "**Avoid direct mutation**",
        "**Split state logically**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Mutating state directly**",
        "**Not using previous state when needed**",
        "**Storing unnecessary data**",
        "**Overusing single state object**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
